00:28:43.489 --> 00:28:48.299
used to select that font is exactly the same.
You didn't have to change anything in your

00:28:48.299 --> 00:28:54.759
page. All of the users of the Google Font
API got this optimization completely for free.

00:28:54.759 --> 00:29:02.659
And that is something that would not be possible,
using the pure CSS at font face. You get that

00:29:02.659 --> 00:29:07.139
because of the dynamic work that the Google
Font API is doing behind the scenes.

00:29:07.139 --> 00:29:13.769
So that's bringing the request down to 29K.
A nice -- you know, something that really

00:29:13.769 --> 00:29:17.140
is practical, even if you're building sites
that are optimized for mobile.

00:29:17.140 --> 00:29:23.570
But of course we weren't satisfied there.
Why are we sending the entire font to build

00:29:23.570 --> 00:29:28.799
this logo when we're only using 10 characters
