API.

00:29:43.149 --> 00:29:49.249
And so you can see it at the bottom, that
we add to the request the exact text that

00:29:49.249 --> 00:29:52.559
we're going to render. Actually, you can use
the letters. They don't have to be in order

00:29:52.559 --> 00:29:56.999
and they don't have to contain duplicates,
but here it's easy to see what we're doing.

00:29:56.999 --> 00:30:02.929
And now the font that you get back is 4.6K.
I mean, it's incredibly tiny. You can use

00:30:02.929 --> 00:30:09.749
this on a mobile device, and it's effectively
instant. Except 4.6K is the version that we

00:30:09.749 --> 00:30:17.559
give to Windows, so you can see in the chart
