00:30:21.350 --> 00:30:24.850
to get there, and again, this is done with
the same HTML snippet. You don't have to do

00:30:24.850 --> 00:30:29.220
anything special to get the mobile Android
and iOS optimization.

00:30:29.220 --> 00:30:35.109
And when both of these optimizations are applied
together, it brings the request down to 2.8K,

00:30:35.109 --> 00:30:43.059
which is just, you know, amazing in terms
of how fast that will transfer over the wire.

00:30:43.059 --> 00:30:50.970
So in this case, it's even significant improvement
over an optimized image for that page.

00:30:50.970 --> 00:30:55.489
So there's lots and lots of benefits of using
this feature. It's fast. Especially for mobile.

00:30:55.489 --> 00:31:00.389
And we heard a lot about Android this morning.
Mobile web is a huge part of the web, and

00:31:00.389 --> 00:31:05.729
growing fast, and so we really want to optimize
sites for mobile web as well.

00:31:05.729 --> 00:31:10.169
You can use one font. You can use one text
equals request for all of the text on your

00:31:10.169 --> 00:31:15.460
page. So if you've got lots of navigation
elements or menus, you can combine all of

00:31:15.460 --> 00:31:20.830
that into one request to the Google Font API,
get one font that renders for all of those

00:31:20.830 --> 00:31:26.210
uses, whereas images would require one image
per use on that page.

00:31:26.210 --> 00:31:30.139
And another thing that we're really excited
about, going forward, is that this technique

00:31:30.139 --> 00:31:34.850
works very well for international fonts. Multilingual
fonts can be huge.

00:31:34.850 --> 00:31:41.109
A Chinese or Japanese font can get into multiple
megabytes. So we're -- all of these -- the

00:31:41.109 --> 00:31:46.119
text equals feature works on all the international
fonts in the Google Font -- Google web font

00:31:46.119 --> 00:31:54.179
service as well, and we think this is really
key to get worldwide adoption of web fonts.

00:31:54.179 --> 00:31:59.389
So I want to step back a little and just go
through all of the things that we're doing

00:31:59.389 --> 00:32:03.830
to make web fonts fast.
In addition to the features that I talked

00:32:03.830 --> 00:32:09.340
about before, the size optimization for mobile
and Mac and the text equals feature, we're

00:32:09.340 --> 00:32:14.179
doing a lot of innovative things behind the
scenes in our serving infrastructure. We're

00:32:14.179 --> 00:32:19.029
setting maximal caching of those fonts. We
can do that because they're open source. There's

00:32:19.029 --> 00:32:25.870
no peg 8 that we need to put in place, so
we can go completely floor to the -- you know,

00:32:25.870 --> 00:32:31.440
foot to the floor to get those fonts as fast
as possible, and that includes our caching

00:32:31.440 --> 00:32:38.210
strategy. That includes across sites.
So if somebody has navigated to a site that

00:32:38.210 --> 00:32:43.950
uses a Google Font and then they navigate
to your site that uses that same font, that

00:32:43.950 --> 00:32:48.119
font will already be in the user's cache and
there isn't even a network request to check

00:32:48.119 --> 00:32:52.840
whether it's in the cache. It just renders
instantly in that case. That's one of the

00:32:52.840 --> 00:32:58.639
reasons we're so excited to see the incredible
increase in adoption that Dave was talking

00:32:58.639 --> 00:33:04.090
about earlier.
The more popular the Google Font service becomes,

00:33:04.090 --> 00:33:10.440
the faster it's going to be.
We, of course, use maximal compression on

00:33:10.440 --> 00:33:15.830
all of our fonts, and today that's including
the WOFF format on all modern browsers. On

00:33:15.830 --> 00:33:21.600
browsers that don't support it, we use different
forms of compression, but we use the maximum

00:33:21.600 --> 00:33:26.679
compression that's available.
I talked about the optimizations, the size

00:33:26.679 --> 00:33:31.789
optimizations for mobile, text equals, and,
you know, don't forget that everything is

00:33:31.789 --> 00:33:36.690
being served from Google's worldwide infrastructure,
so we've got data centers around the world

00:33:36.690 --> 00:33:40.799
and you'll get the fonts served to the user
from their nearest data center, no matter

00:33:40.799 --> 00:33:46.690
where they are and no matter where the site
developer is.

00:33:46.690 --> 00:33:52.159
So, you know, we're hard at work. That's a
big part of what we do is building the fastest

00:33:52.159 --> 00:33:55.190
infrastructure for serving web fonts that's
possible.

00:33:55.190 --> 00:34:01.049
But the integration for you is easy and quick.
The 30 seconds that you saw is all you need

00:34:01.049 --> 00:34:07.090
