&gt;&gt;Raph Levien: Yes, there is a reason. And
it's, basically, the import rule for CSS actually

00:46:27.150 --> 00:46:33.240
causes some blocking that you can serialize
the loading of the different CSS elements

00:46:33.240 --> 00:46:40.130
on some especially older browsers. So, if
you are designing primarily for newer modern

00:46:40.130 --> 00:46:42.830
browsers, then doing it completely in CSS
is a great option.

